RELATIONSHIP VALUES CLARIFICATION EXERCISE

Instructions: Read through the list of values below and select your top 10 most important values in a romantic relationship. Then narrow down to your top 5 non-negotiables.

CORE VALUES LIST:
- Honesty
- Trust
- Respect
- Communication
- Emotional Availability
- Kindness
- Compassion
- Humor/Lightheartedness
- Intelligence
- Ambition/Drive
- Independence
- Commitment
- Loyalty
- Affection/Physical Touch
- Shared Laughter
- Similar Life Goals
- Family Orientation
- Spirituality/Shared Beliefs
- Adventure/Novelty
- Stability/Security
- Growth Mindset
- Vulnerability
- Accountability
- Empathy
- Patience
- Forgiveness
- Shared Values
- Emotional Safety
- Fun/Playfulness
- Supportiveness
- Reliability
- Authenticity
- Equality/Partnership
- Sexual Compatibility
- Communication Style Match
- Conflict Resolution Skills
- Emotional Intelligence
- Similar Energy Levels
- Respect for Boundaries
- Financial Compatibility
- Similar Social Preferences
- Intellectual Stimulation
- Emotional Maturity
- Generosity
- Gratitude
- Humility
- Curiosity
- Creativity
- Passion
- Purpose/Direction
- Nurturing/Caring
- Protectiveness
- Jealousy Management
- Trust Building
- Consistency
- Predictability
- Spontaneity
- Adventure Seeking
- Calm Presence
- Excitement/Energy
- Depth/Meaning
- Lightness/Joy
- Stability/Routine
- Flexibility/Adaptability

STEP 1: Circle your top 10 values
STEP 2: From your top 10, mark your top 5 with a star
STEP 3: For each of your top 5, write a brief explanation of why it's non-negotiable for you

